'''Notes:'''
# {{note|tar-compression-w}} Tar implementations call the external programs gzip and bzip2, 7z, xz, ... to perform compression; these external programs usually come with systems that contain tar.
# {{note|writing-tugzip}} Requires rar.exe from WinRAR.
# {{note|writing-winzip}} Requires external program. [http://www.winzip.com/wzdifs.htm More info]
# {{note|writing-tugzipace}} Requires Ace32.exe from WinAce.
# {{note|Extractor}} The Extractor and XAD are not included in this list because they only expand archives.
# {{note|ALZip}} ALZip can also write to the following formats: BH, JAR, and LZH
# {{note|zipgenius-updating}} Updating archives is not supported.[http://www.zipgenius.it/eng/?page_id=3]
# {{note|zipgenius-external}} Requires external program.[http://www.zipgenius.it/eng/?page_id=3]
# {{note|StuffIt}}Stuffit supported file formats [http://my.smithmicro.com/stuffitcompression/fileformats.html]
# {{note|writing-ark}} Ark is a [[frontend|front-end]] only and requires appropriate command-line programs be installed. Programs like bzip2, gzip, tar, zip usually come with systems that contain Ark; writing in [[.rar]] format requires a [[non-free software|commercial]] program. [http://utils.kde.org/projects/ark/]
# {{note|writing-xarchiver}} Xarchiver is a front-end only and requires appropriate command-line programs be installed. Programs like bzip2, gzip, tar, zip usually come with systems that contain Xarchiver; writing in .rar format requires a commercial program. [http://xarchiver.xfce.org/doc/ch01.html][http://xarchiver.xfce.org/doc/ch03s03.html]
# {{note|writing-fileroller}} File-Roller is a front-end only and requires appropriate command-line programs be installed. Programs like bzip2, gzip, tar, zip usually come with systems that contain File-Roller. writing in .rar format requires a commercial program.[http://fileroller.sourceforge.net/features.html]
# {{note|writing-keka}} Keka version under development is able to create ISO and DMG files.

==== Uncommon archive format support ====
PeaZip has full support for various LPAQ and [[PAQ]] formats, QUAD and BALZ (highly efficient [[ROLZ]] based compressors), [[FreeArc]] format, and for its native [[List of archive formats|PEA]] format.

7-Zip includes read support for [[.msi]], [[cpio]] and [[xar (archiver)|xar]], plus Apple's [[Apple Disk Image|dmg]]/[[Hierarchical File System|HFS]] disk images and the [[deb (file format)|deb]]/[[RPM Package Manager|.rpm]] package distribution formats; beta versions (9.07 onwards) have full support for the LZMA2-compressed .[[xz]] format.<ref name="7zipHistory"/>

